			<div type="edition" xml:lang="san-Latn" rendition="class:83225 maturity:83211"><!--
Comments below by Csaba Kiss and Dániel Balogh (BD) are offered "as is" and do not represent a thoroughly researched or considered opinion.
--><!--
1 Katare, S.L., 'Sirpur plates of Mahā-Sudevarāja',
Epigraphia Indica vol XXXI, pp. 103-108
2 Shastri, A. M., Inscriptions of the Śarabhapurīyas,
Pāṇḍuvaṁśins and Somavaṁśins, Part II Inscriptions,
Motilal Bandarsidass, Delhi, 1995, pp. 35-38
--><div type="textpart" n="A"><head xml:lang="eng">Seal</head>
<lg n="1" met="anuṣṭubh">
<lb
n="1"/>
<l n="a">prasanna-tanayasyedaṁ</l>
<l n="b">vikkramotkhāta-vidviṣa<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied></l>
<lb
n="2"/>
<l n="c">śrīmato jayarājasya</l>
<l n="d">śāsanaṁ ripu-śāsana<choice><sic><unclear>ṁ</unclear></sic><corr>M</corr></choice></l><!--
Katare thinks that that seal originally belonged to another
set of copper plates. The Ed. disagrees. Shastri cites other opinions
and finally agrees with Katare.
--></lg>
				</div>
				<div type="textpart" n="B"><head xml:lang="eng">Plates</head>
<p><pb

n="1v"/><lb
n="1"/><g type="mangala"/>
svasti<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied>
śarabha-purād vikkramopanata-sāmanta-ma<supplied reason="lost" evidence="parallel">kuṭa-cūḍā-maṇi</supplied>-
<lb
n="2"/>prabhā-prasekāmbu-dhauta-pāda-yugalo ripu-vilāsi<supplied reason="lost" evidence="parallel">nī-sīmantoddharaṇa</supplied>-
<lb
n="3"/>hetur vvasu-vasudhā-go-pradaḫ parama-bhāgava<supplied reason="lost" evidence="parallel">to mātā-pitr̥-pādā</supplied><lb
n="4" break="no"/>nuddhyātaś śrī-mahā-sudeva-rājaḥ
						<choice><unclear>c</unclear><unclear>v</unclear></choice>u<gap reason="lost" precision="low" quantity="9" unit="character"/><!--
Katare reads vu here, Shastri cu. Name of donated village and district lost. D. Balogh: cu seems more likely; elsewhere in these plates v consistently appears to have a square body, c an oblong one.
--><lb
n="5" break="no"/>vake prativāsi-kuṭumbinas samājñā<supplied reason="lost" evidence="parallel">payati| viditam astu vo</supplied><!--
L5. Village is "Keśavaka" says Shastri.
--><!--
L5. ā in samājñ- is "is indicated by the downward elongation of the right
vertical of the letter m". Shastri
--><lb
n="6"/>yathāsmābhir ayaṁ grāmas
t<choice><sic>r̥</sic><corr>ri</corr></choice>daśapati-sa<supplied reason="lost" evidence="parallel">dana-sukha-pratiṣṭhā-karo</supplied>
						<pb

n="2r"/><lb
n="7"/>yāvad ravi-śaśi-tārā-kiraṇa-pratihata-ghorāndhakāraṁ jagad avatiṣṭha<lb
n="8" break="no"/>te tāvad upabhogyas sanidhis sopanidhir
acāṭa-bhaṭa-prāveśyas sarvva-ka<lb
n="9" break="no"/>ra-visarjjita<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied> pūrvvaṁ
nanna-pādais taittirīya-pārāśara-sagotra-brāhma<lb
n="10" break="no"/>ṇa-kāraṇika-kansippasvāmin<choice><sic>o</sic><corr>e</corr></choice><!--
L10. Both Shastri and Katare emend to svāmine.
-->datta Idānīm apy asmābhir api
<lb
n="11"/>mahā-devī-rāja-kulānāṁ vijñāpyā<choice><sic>s</sic><corr>t</corr></choice><!--
L11. Katare emends to vijñāpyāt. Shastri: "Read: vijñāpya tāmra-"
-->tām<surplus>b</surplus>ra-śāsanī-kr̥taḥ te yūyaṁ E<lb
n="12" break="no"/>vam upalabhyāsyājñā-śravaṇa-vidheyā bhūtvā yathocitaṁ bhoga-bhāga<pb

n="2v" break="no"/><lb
n="13" break="no"/>m upanayantas sukhaṁ prativatsyatha<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied><!--
L13. Katare emends to prativatsatha.
-->bhaviṣyataś ca bhūmipān anu<lb
n="14" break="no"/>darśayati|
</p>
<lg n="1" met="vasantatilakā">
<l n="a">dānād viśiṣṭam anupālana-jaṁ purāṇā</l>
<l n="b">dharmmeṣu niścita-
<lb
n="15"/>dhiyaḫ pravadanti dharmma<choice><sic>ṁ</sic><corr>M</corr></choice></l>


<l n="c">tasmā<supplied reason="omitted">d</supplied> dvijāya su-viśuddha-kula-śrutāya</l>
<l n="d">dattāṁ<!--
L15. Shastri suggests "tasmād [d*] dvijāya", which must be a typo.
--><lb
n="16"/>bhuvaṁ bhavatu vo matir eva goptu<supplied reason="omitted">M</supplied>||</l>
</lg>
<p>tad bhavadbhir apy eṣā dattir anu<lb
n="17" break="no"/>pālay<choice><sic>ī</sic><corr>i</corr></choice>tavyā<!--
Katare reads anupālayitavyā.
-->vyāsa-gītāṁś cātra ślokān udāharanti</p>
<lg n="2" met="indravajrā"><!--
Garuḍapurāṇa 2.42.4
-->
<l n="a">agner apatyaṁ pra<lb
n="18" break="no"/>thamaṁ suvarṇṇaṁ</l>
<l n="b">bhūr vvaiṣṇavī sūryya-sutāś ca gāvaḥ</l>


<l n="c">dattās trayas te
								<pb

n="3r" break="no"/>
<lb
n="19" break="no"/>na bhavanti lokā<surplus>ḥ</surplus></l>
<l n="d">yaẖ kāñcanaṁ gāṁ ca mahī<unclear>ṁ</unclear> ca dadyāt</l><!--
L19. In Shastri, ṁ is not unclear; it is supplied. D. Balogh: I see no trace of anusvāra in the facsimile in EI, but we can give the engraver the benefit of doubt.
--></lg>
<lg n="3" met="anuṣṭubh">
<l n="a">ṣaṣṭi-varṣa-sa<lb
n="20" break="no"/>hasrāṇi</l>
<l n="b">svargge modati bhūmi-daḥ</l>


<l n="c">Acchettā cānumantā ca</l>
<l n="d">tāny e<lb
n="21" break="no"/>va narake vaseT</l>
</lg>
<lg n="4" met="anuṣṭubh">
<l n="a">bahubhir vvasudhā dattā</l>
<l n="b">rājabhis sagarādibhiḥ</l>


<l n="c">yasya <lb
n="22" break="no"/>yasya yadā
bhūmi<choice><sic>ḥ</sic><corr>s</corr></choice></l>
<l n="d">tasya tasya tadā phala<choice><sic>ṁ</sic><corr>M</corr></choice></l>
</lg>
<lg n="5" met="anuṣṭubh">
<l n="a">sva-dattāṁ para-dattāṁ vā</l>
<l n="b"><lb
n="23"/>yatnād rakṣa yudhiṣṭhira</l>


<l n="c">mahī<choice><sic>t</sic><corr>ṁ</corr></choice>
mahimatāñ śreṣṭha</l><!--
v5c. In other inscriptions others correct it, probably wrongly, to mahīmatāṁ.
-->
<l n="d">dānāc chreyo <supplied reason="subaudible">’</supplied>nupāla
<lb
n="24" break="no"/>nam</l>
</lg>
<p>iti<supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> sva-mukhājñayā
pravarddhamāna-v<choice><sic>ī</sic><corr>i</corr></choice>jaya-sa<choice><sic>v</sic><corr>ṁ</corr></choice>va <num value="7">7</num> dvi-bhādra-di <num value="10"><g type="numeral">10</g></num></p>
<p><pb

n="3v"/><lb
n="25"/>U<choice><sic>kt</sic><corr>tk</corr></choice>īrṇṇaṁ droṇasi<choice><sic>ṅgh</sic><corr>ṁh</corr></choice>e<choice><sic>ṇ</sic><corr>n</corr></choice>a||<!--
L25. This is engraved in the middle of the plate.
--></p>
